	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Would official programming documentation be welcomed in NesDev?</div>
<br />
<br />Only if it's legal, which pretty much means "no". Any documentation produced by Nintendo will be at the very least copyrighted, and I'd be highly skeptical of any claims that Nintendo had allowed it to be freely distributed. At this point, our own reverse-engineering effort is not far from being complete, and the information is more reliable than any documentation (except perhaps one marked up with notes and corrections by a NES programmer).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


