	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Are public patents considered trade secrets?</div><br />No. Patents are publications of the United States government and are not subject to copyright or trade secret law.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">It's (+)control pad and not (+)"D-Pad"? (Also was the D originally for directional or digital?)</div><br />Nintendo has never called it the D-Pad; that's a Sega term. It's been the Control Pad since 1985.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Do you know what NP did call the discrete logic?</div>
<br />"Logic Gates".

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


