		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">That's true that any document even obtained through legitimate (fair) means would have been originally leaked in breach of somebody's NDA</div><br />It's not the NDA in general that's the problem, it's that any documentation, even that bought in a public bookstore, would be copyrighted material and thus subject to whatever restrictions the holder has decided on. Though NDA/trade secret adds another twist, in that the information itself can't be shared, regardless of the wording.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Component names and high level descriptions should be fair however since the act of transfer of information is ambiguous.</div>
<br />They might be interesting, though they'd be yet another alternate name for whatever they are commonly called. And if they are as bad as the names for the Game Boy sound registers (NR12, NR25, etc.), I'll pass! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

